info.title: Vercel API
info.description: Vercel combines the best developer experience with an obsessive focus on end-user performance. Our platform enables frontend teams to do their best work.

name.description: The name of this access group.

createdAt.description: Timestamp in milliseconds when the access group was created.

teamId.description: ID of the team that this access group belongs to.

updatedAt.description: Timestamp in milliseconds when the access group was last updated.

membersCount.description: Number of members in the access group.

projectsCount.description: Number of projects in the access group.

ACLAction.description: Enum containing the actions that can be performed against a resource. Group operations are included.

oneOf.description: TODO: The following types will eventually be exported by a more relevant package.

count.description: Amount of items in the current page.

next.description: Timestamp that must be used to request the next page.

prev.description: Timestamp that must be used to request the previous page.

Pagination.description: This object contains information related to the pagination of the current request, including the necessary parameters to get the next or previous page of data.

id.description: This is not the token itself, but rather an id to identify the token by
The unique identifier of the Event.

text.description: The human-readable text of the Event.

start.description: The index of where the entity begins within the `text` (inclusive).

end.description: The index of where the entity ends within the `text` (non-inclusive).

items.description: A list of "entities" within the event `text`. Useful for enhancing the displayed text with additional styling and links.

entities.description: A list of "entities" within the event `text`. Useful for enhancing the displayed text with additional styling and links.

createdAt.description: Timestamp (in milliseconds) of when the event was generated.

user.description: Metadata for the User who generated the event.

userId.description: The unique identifier of the User who generated the event.

UserEvent.description: Array of events generated by the User.

limited.description: Property indicating that this Team data contains only limited information, due to the authentication token missing privileges to read the full Team data. Re-login with the Team's configured SAML Single Sign-On provider in order to upgrade the authentication token with the necessary privileges.

type.description: The Identity Provider "type", for example Okta.

connectedAt.description: Timestamp (in milliseconds) of when the configuration was connected.

lastReceivedWebhookEvent.description: Timestamp (in milliseconds) of when the last webhook event was received from WorkOS.

connection.description: Information for the SAML Single Sign-On configuration.

type.description: The Identity Provider "type", for example Okta.

connectedAt.description: Timestamp (in milliseconds) of when the configuration was connected.

lastReceivedWebhookEvent.description: Timestamp (in milliseconds) of when the last webhook event was received from WorkOS.

directory.description: Information for the Directory Sync configuration.

enforced.description: When `true`, interactions with the Team **must** be done with an authentication token that has been authenticated with the Team's SAML Single Sign-On provider.

saml.description: When "Single Sign-On (SAML)" is configured, this object contains information that allows the client-side to identify whether or not this Team has SAML enforced.

slug.description: The Team's slug, which is unique across the Vercel platform.

name.description: Name associated with the Team account, or `null` if none has been provided.

avatar.description: The ID of the file used as avatar for this Team.

membership.description: The membership of the authenticated User in relation to the Team.

created.description: Will remain undocumented. Remove in v3 API.

createdAt.description: UNIX timestamp (in milliseconds) when the Team was created.

TeamLimited.description: A limited form of data representing a Team, due to the authentication token missing privileges to read the full Team data.

softBlock.description: When the User account has been "soft blocked", this property will contain the date when the restriction was enacted, and the identifier for why.
